#===========================================================================#
#                            Getting Started                                #
#===========================================================================#
1. Pull project from source control:

        [vagrant@localhost] cd src
        [vagrant@localhost] svn --username=<svn-user> co <svn-url> stealth_marketplace

2. Change directory to project root:

        [vagrant@localhost] cd src/stealth_marketplace

3. Install required ruby version if instructed to do so instructed by rvm:

        [vagrant@localhost] rvm install <version>

4. Update AWS credentials and config by editing:

        ~/.aws/credentials
        ~/.aws/config

5. Set a unique name for AWS test resources by performing the following:

        echo "<a unique name>" >> ~/.rspec_user_name

6. Execute your first test run:

        [vagrant@localhost] cd ~/src/stealth_marketplace
        [vagrant@localhost] bin/rake
        [vagrant@localhost] bin/rspec


7.  If you wish to use Kitchen for cookbook testing perform the following.

        i.   Copy an AWS private key to the vagrant box.
        ii.  Edit .bashrc to set AWS_SSH_* environment variables.
        iii. Load the new environment vars using . ~/.bashrc 

8. Optionally remove this message by removing content of /etc/motd 
